The paper deals with the construction of a geometric graph (Manhattan network) for a set of points in the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of Steiner points, which are commonly used in algorithms for constructing geometric graphs, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the size and planarity of the constructed graph, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GR (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper involves the computation of shortest paths, which is a topic in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
